<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="191" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d191fn1">Sent to the United States Naval
                                Attaché, London, via Navy channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-30">July 30, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>For the <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss> from the
                            President personal and secret Number 333.</p>
                        <pb facs="0520" n="406" xml:id="pg_406"/>
                        <p>Your Number 385.<note n="2" xml:id="d191fn2">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_403">p.
                                403</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>I have wired Harriman to come if possible.<note n="3" xml:id="d191fn3">Roosevelt’s telegram to Harriman, July 30, 1943, and Harriman’s
                                reply of August 2, 1943, stating that he was arranging to travel
                                with the “Colonel”, are not printed (Harriman Papers).</note> Lew
                            Douglas will be with us.</p>
                        <p>Delighted Leathers is coming.</p>
                        <p>We will be waiting for you and personal staff at H.P.<note n="4" xml:id="d191fn4">Hyde Park.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>